.SH NAME
HTMLDetailsElement \- HTMLDetailsElement
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]HTMLDetailsElement\f[B]\f[R] interface provides special
properties (beyond the regular \f[CR]HTMLElement\f[R] interface it also
has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating
\f[CR]<details>\f[R] elements.
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
\f[I]Inherits properties from its parent, \f[CI]HTMLElement\f[I].\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]HTMLDetailsElement.name\f[R]
A string reflecting the \f[CR]name\f[R] HTML attribute, which allows you
to create a group of mutually\-exclusive \f[CR]<details>\f[R] elements.
Opening one of the named \f[CR]<details>\f[R] elements of this group
causes other elements of the group to close.
.TP
\f[B]HTMLDetailsElement.open\f[R]
A boolean value reflecting the \f[CR]open\f[R] HTML attribute,
indicating whether or not the element\[cq]s contents (not counting the
\f[CR]<summary>\f[R]) is to be shown to the user.
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
\f[I]No specific method; inherits methods from its parent,
\f[CI]HTMLElement\f[I].\f[R]
.SH EVENTS
\f[I]Inherits events from its parent interface,
\f[CI]HTMLElement\f[I].\f[R]
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Log chapters as they are opened and closed
This example uses the \f[CR]HTMLElement\f[R] \f[CR]toggle\f[R] event to
add and remove chapters from a log aside as they are opened and closed.
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]section\f[R] id=\[dq]summaries\[dq]>
  <\f[B]p\f[R]>Chapter summaries:</\f[B]p\f[R]>
  <\f[B]details\f[R] id=\[dq]ch1\[dq]>
    <\f[B]summary\f[R]>Chapter I</\f[B]summary\f[R]>
    Philosophy reproves Boethius for the foolishness of his complaints against
    Fortune. Her very nature is caprice.
  </\f[B]details\f[R]>
  <\f[B]details\f[R] id=\[dq]ch2\[dq]>
    <\f[B]summary\f[R]>Chapter II</\f[B]summary\f[R]>
    Philosophy in Fortune\[aq]s name replies to Boethius\[aq] reproaches, and proves
    that the gifts of Fortune are hers to give and to take away.
  </\f[B]details\f[R]>
  <\f[B]details\f[R] id=\[dq]ch3\[dq]>
    <\f[B]summary\f[R]>Chapter III</\f[B]summary\f[R]>
    Boethius falls back upon his present sense of misery. Philosophy reminds him
    of the brilliancy of his former fortunes.
  </\f[B]details\f[R]>
</\f[B]section\f[R]>
<\f[B]aside\f[R] id=\[dq]log\[dq]>
  <\f[B]p\f[R]>Open chapters:</\f[B]p\f[R]>
  <\f[B]div\f[R] data\-id=\[dq]ch1\[dq] hidden>I</\f[B]div\f[R]>
  <\f[B]div\f[R] data\-id=\[dq]ch2\[dq] hidden>II</\f[B]div\f[R]>
  <\f[B]div\f[R] data\-id=\[dq]ch3\[dq] hidden>III</\f[B]div\f[R]>
</\f[B]aside\f[R]>
